{"title_page": "Sandai", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=March 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film|\n| name = Sandai\n| image = Mahamagam-6.jpg\n| director = [[Sakthi Chidambaram]]\n| writer = [[Ravi Mariya]]<br /><small>'''(Dialogue)'''</small>\n| story = Sakthi Chidambaram\n| based on=\n| screenplay = Sakthi Chidambaram\n| starring = [[Sundar C]]<br>[[Nadhiya]]<br>[[Namitha]]<br>[[Ramya Raj]]<br>[[Suja]]<br>[[Napoleon (actor)|Napoleon]]<br>[[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]]<br>[[Lalu Alex]]<br>[[Mithun Tejasvi]]\n| producer = Radha Sakthi Chidambaram\n| music =  [[Dhina]]\n| cinematography = K. S. Selva Raj\n| editing = G. Sasikumar\n| studio = Cinema Paradise\n| distributor    = Cinema Paradise\n| released = {{Film date|2008|03|21|df=y}}\n| runtime =\n| language = Tamil\n| country = India\n| budget =\n| website =\n}}\n'''''Sandai''''' ''(English: Fight)'' is a 2008 [[Tamil language|Tamil]] [[action film|action]] [[drama film]] directed by [[Sakthi Chidambaram]]. The film stars [[Sundar C]], [[Nadhiya]], [[Namitha]], and [[Ramya Raj]] in the lead roles, while [[Napoleon (actor)|Napoleon]], [[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]], [[Lalu Alex]], and [[Mithun Tejasvi]], among others, play supporting roles. The music was composed by [[Dhina]] with cinematography done by K. S. Selva Raj and editing by G. Sasikumar. The film released on 21 March 2008 and was dubbed in Hindi as \"Jungbaaz\".\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Sundar C]] as Kathiresan (Kaththi)\n* [[Nadhiya]] as Thangalakshmi\n* [[Namitha]] as Seemakal Chinnakilli\n* [[Ramya Raj]] as Abhi\n* [[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]] as Mani / Thangapandi, the village chieftain\n* [[Napoleon (actor)|Napoleon]] as  District Collector Kamaraj (Thangalakshmi's husband)\n* [[Lalu Alex]] as Paalpandi, Kathiresan's father\n* [[Mithun Tejasvi]]\n* [[Dhandapani]]\n* [[Ravi Mariya]]\n* [[Rajkapoor]]\n* [[Thalapathy Dinesh]]\n* [[Vichu Vishwanath]]\n* [[Meera Krishnan]] as Kathiresan's's mother\n* [[Paravai Muniyamma]] as Kathirvel's grandmother\n* [[Jyothi Lakshmi]] as Mani's mother\n* [[Delhi Kumar]] as Tha's father\n* [[Uma Padmanabhan]] as DSP\n* [[Suja Varunee]] as item number\n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nIt was announced in 2007 that Sundar C. will team up with Sakthi Chidambaram for an action comedy film. During the launch, the film was initially titled as ''Porukki'',<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/sep-07-01/04-09-07-simbu.html</ref> however as the title was said to be derogatory, the titles like ''Adhirudhula'' and ''Mahamagam''<ref>https://www.filmibeat.com/tamil/news/2007/porukki-becomes-mahamagam-190907.html</ref> were considered before the team preferred to name the film as ''Sandai''.<ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/porukki-is-now-adhirudhilla-tamil-news-33400</ref><ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/all-in-the-name-of%C3%82%C2%85-a-film-ii-tamil-news-55457</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Sandai \n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Dhina]]\n| cover        = \n| released     = 1 February 2008 \n| recorded     = 2008 \n| genre        = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length       = 26:11\n| label        = T-Series\n| producer     = Dhina\n| prev_title   = [[Kannum Kannum]]\n| prev_year    = 2008\n| next_title   = [[Dindigul Sarathy]]\n| next_year    = 2008\n}}\n\nMusic is composed by [[Dhina]] and Released on [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Sanda - Dheena - Download or Listen Free - Saavn |url=https://www.saavn.com/album/sanda/nmVWuHPU3qQ_ |accessdate=14 November 2018 |date=1 January 2009}}</ref>\n\n{{tracklist|\n|extra_column=Singer(s)\n|headline = Track-List\n|total_length=26:11\n|title1=Pokkirina|extra1=[[Silambarasan]]| lyrics1 = [[Na. Muthukumar]]|length1= 4:50\n|title2=October Madathil|extra2=[[Shaan (singer)|Shaan]], [[Rita Thyagarajan|Rita]]| lyrics2 = [[Ravi Mariya]]|length2=5:49 \n|title3=Vaadi En|extra3=[[Sundar C.]]| lyrics3 = [[Gangai Amaran]]|length3=5:26\n|title4=Aathadi|extra4=Dev Prakash| lyrics4 = Na. Muthukumar|length4=4:37\n|title5=Maduraikara|extra5=[[Udit Narayan]], [[Anuradha Sriram]]| lyrics5 = [[Sakthi Chidambaram]]|length5=5:29\n|title6=Sanda Ah Odayuthu Odayuthu|extra6=Narendra| lyrics6 = [[Ramajogayya Sastry]]|length6=4:21 \n}}\n\n==Reception==\n''Rediff'' called it \"illogical\" and stated that \"Just suspend all logic and reason before settling for this age-old mother-in-law/son-in-law battle movies on the lines of Poova Thalaiya and Mappillai.\"<ref>http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/sssandai/20080324.htm</ref> ''Behindwoods'' wrote \"You need no introduction to the Shakthi Chidambaram brand of cinema- he makes movies purely for entertainment and most often they work. This time the director who had formerly specialized in Sathyaraj starrers has teamed up with Sundar C to provide Sandai.\"<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-1/sandai-review.html</ref> ''Sify'' wrote \"Here is regressive piece of kitsch, with over-the-top loud performances. The plot degenerates into a farce in the second half of this tedious film as it tumbles to an all?s-well-that- concludes-well end\".<ref>http://www.sify.com/movies/sandai-review-tamil-pclw7lhhgfacd.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sakthi Chidambaram}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2000s action films]]\n[[Category:2008 films]]\n[[Category:2000s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n[[Category:Indian action films]]\n[[Category:Masala films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=March 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n{{Infobox film|\n| name = Sandai\n| image = Mahamagam-6.jpg\n| director = [[Sakthi Chidambaram]]\n| writer = [[Ravi Mariya]]<br /><small>'''(Dialogue)'''</small>\n| story = Sakthi Chidambaram\n| based on=\n| screenplay = Sakthi Chidambaram\n| starring = [[Sundar C]]<br>[[Nadhiya]]<br>[[Namitha]]<br>[[Ramya Raj]]<br>[[Suja]]<br>[[Napoleon (actor)|Napoleon]]<br>[[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]]<br>[[Lalu Alex]]<br>[[Mithun Tejasvi]]\n| producer = Radha Sakthi Chidambaram\n| music =  [[Dhina]]\n| cinematography = K. S. Selva Raj\n| editing = G. Sasikumar\n| studio = Cinema Paradise\n| distributor    = Cinema Paradise\n| released = {{Film date|2008|03|21|df=y}}\n| runtime =\n| language = Tamil\n| country = India\n| budget =\n| website =\n}}\n'''''Sandai''''' ''(English: Fight)'' is a 2008 [[Tamil language|Tamil]] [[action film|action]] [[drama film]] directed by [[Sakthi Chidambaram]]. The film stars [[Sundar C]], [[Nadhiya]], [[Namitha]], and [[Ramya Raj]] in the lead roles, while [[Napoleon (actor)|Napoleon]], [[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]], [[Lalu Alex]], and [[Mithun Tejasvi]], among others, play supporting roles. The music was composed by [[Dhina]] with cinematography done by K. S. Selva Raj and editing by G. Sasikumar. The film released on 21 March 2008 and was dubbed in Hindi as \"Jungbaaz\".\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Sundar C]] as Kathiresan (Kaththi)\n* [[Nadhiya]] as Thangalakshmi\n* [[Namitha]] as Seemakal Chinnakilli\n* [[Ramya Raj]] as Abhi\n* [[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]] as Mani / Thangapandi, the village chieftain\n* [[Napoleon (actor)|Napoleon]] as  District Collector Kamaraj (Thangalakshmi's husband)\n* [[Lalu Alex]] as Paalpandi, Kathiresan's father\n* [[Mithun Tejasvi]]\n* [[Dhandapani]]\n* [[Ravi Mariya]]\n* [[Rajkapoor]]\n* [[Thalapathy Dinesh]]\n* [[Vichu Vishwanath]]\n* [[Meera Krishnan]] as Kathiresan's's mother\n* [[Paravai Muniyamma]] as Kathirvel's grandmother\n* [[Jyothi Lakshmi]] as Mani's mother\n* [[Delhi Kumar]] as Tha's father\n* [[Uma Padmanabhan]] as DSP\n* [[Suja Varunee]] as item number\n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nIt was announced in 2007 that Sundar C. will team up with Sakthi Chidambaram for an action comedy film. During the launch, the film was initially titled as ''Porukki'',<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/sep-07-01/04-09-07-simbu.html</ref> however as the title was said to be derogatory, the titles like ''Adhirudhula'' and ''Mahamagam''<ref>https://www.filmibeat.com/tamil/news/2007/porukki-becomes-mahamagam-190907.html</ref> were considered before the team preferred to name the film as ''Sandai''.<ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/porukki-is-now-adhirudhilla-tamil-news-33400</ref><ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/all-in-the-name-of%C3%82%C2%85-a-film-ii-tamil-news-55457</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Sandai \n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Dhina]]\n| cover        = \n| released     = 1 February 2008 \n| recorded     = 2008 \n| genre        = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length       = 26:11\n| label        = T-Series\n| producer     = Dhina\n| prev_title   = [[Kannum Kannum]]\n| prev_year    = 2008\n| next_title   = [[Dindigul Sarathy]]\n| next_year    = 2008\n}}\n\nMusic is composed by [[Dhina]] and Released on [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Sanda - Dheena - Download or Listen Free - Saavn |url=https://www.saavn.com/album/sanda/nmVWuHPU3qQ_ |accessdate=14 November 2018 |date=1 January 2009}}</ref>\n\n{{tracklist|\n|extra_column=Singer(s)\n|headline = Track-List\n|total_length=26:11\n|title1=Pokkirina|extra1=[[Silambarasan]]| lyrics1 = [[Na. Muthukumar]]|length1= 4:50\n|title2=October Madathil|extra2=[[Shaan (singer)|Shaan]], [[Rita Thyagarajan|Rita]]| lyrics2 = [[Ravi Mariya]]|length2=5:49 \n|title3=Vaadi En|extra3=[[Sundar C.]]| lyrics3 = [[Gangai Amaran]]|length3=5:26\n|title4=Aathadi|extra4=Dev Prakash| lyrics4 = Na. Muthukumar|length4=4:37\n|title5=Maduraikara|extra5=[[Udit Narayan]], [[Anuradha Sriram]]| lyrics5 = [[Sakthi Chidambaram]]|length5=5:29\n|title6=Sanda Ah Odayuthu Odayuthu|extra6=Narendra| lyrics6 = [[Ramajogayya Sastry]]|length6=4:21 \n}}\n\n==Reception==\n''Rediff'' called it \"illogical\" and stated that \"Just suspend all logic and reason before settling for this age-old mother-in-law/son-in-law battle movies on the lines of Poova Thalaiya and Mappillai.\"<ref>http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/sssandai/20080324.htm</ref> ''Behindwoods'' wrote \"You need no introduction to the Shakthi Chidambaram brand of cinema- he makes movies purely for entertainment and most often they work. This time the director who had formerly specialized in Sathyaraj starrers has teamed up with Sundar C to provide Sandai.\"<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-reviews/reviews-1/sandai-review.html</ref> ''Sify'' wrote \"Here is regressive piece of kitsch, with over-the-top loud performances. The plot degenerates into a farce in the second half of this tedious film as it tumbles to an all?s-well-that- concludes-well end\".<ref>http://www.sify.com/movies/sandai-review-tamil-pclw7lhhgfacd.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sakthi Chidambaram}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2000s action films]]\n[[Category:2008 films]]\n[[Category:2000s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n[[Category:Indian action films]]\n[[Category:Masala films]]\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe", "comment": "Update date format tag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sandai"}
